Brain Tumor Segmentation Using Convolutional Neural Networks in MRI Images.

Pereira S, Pinto A, Alves V, Silva CA.

Among brain tumors, gliomas are the most common and aggressive, leading to a 
very short life expectancy in their highest grade. Thus, treatment planning is a 
key stage to improve the quality of life of oncological patients. Magnetic 
resonance imaging (MRI) is a widely used imaging technique to assess these 
tumors, but the large amount of data produced by MRI prevents manual 
